## 🧠 Overview

This project implements a **production-grade RAG pipeline** that answers natural language questions over a large document corpus. Unlike simple RAG systems that rely solely on semantic similarity, this system combines **dense vector search** (semantic) with **sparse BM25 search** (keyword) and applies **Cohere re-ranking** to select the most relevant context before passing it to GPT-4o for answer generation.

**Problem it solves:** Standard RAG systems fail when queries use exact keywords not captured in embeddings, or when semantically similar but irrelevant documents pollute the context window. Hybrid search + re-ranking fixes both.

**Use case demonstrated:** Enterprise knowledge base Q&A over 50,000+ PDF/text documents with sub-2-second end-to-end response times.

